DBA Roadmap (Zero to Hero)
│
├── 1. Basics of OS and Networking
│   ├── Operating Systems
│   │   ├── Linux (Primary for database servers)
│   │   ├── Windows Server (For MS SQL, Oracle)
│   └── Networking
│       ├── TCP/IP, Ports, Protocols
│       ├── DNS and IP Management
│       └── VPN, Proxy
│
├── 2. Fundamentals of Databases
│   ├── Relational Databases
│   │   ├── Concepts: Tables, Columns, Rows, Relationships
│   │   ├── Database Normalization
│   │   └── ACID Properties (Atomicity, Consistency, Isolation, Durability)
│   ├── SQL Basics
│   │   ├── SELECT, INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE
│   │   ├── Joins (INNER, LEFT, RIGHT, FULL)
│   │   ├── Subqueries, Views, Indexes
│   │   └── Transactions, Locking
│   └── NoSQL Basics (For non-relational databases)
│       ├── Key-Value Stores (Redis)
│       ├── Document Stores (MongoDB)
│       ├── Columnar Stores (Cassandra)
│       └── Graph Databases (Neo4j)
│
├── 3. Database Installation and Configuration
│   ├── Relational Database Management Systems (RDBMS)
│   │   ├── MySQL/MariaDB Installation
│   │   ├── PostgreSQL Installation
│   │   ├── Oracle Database Installation
│   │   └── MS SQL Server Installation
│   ├── Configuration
│   │   ├── Default Settings vs. Customization
│   │   ├── Memory, CPU, and Disk Configuration
│   │   └── Performance Tuning (Buffer Pool, Query Cache)
│   └── NoSQL Databases
│       ├── MongoDB Installation
│       ├── Cassandra Installation
│       └── Redis Installation
│
├── 4. Backup and Recovery
│   ├── Backup Strategies
│   │   ├── Full, Differential, Incremental
│   │   ├── Point-in-Time Recovery
│   │   └── Backup Encryption and Compression
│   ├── Tools for Backup
│   │   ├── MySQLdump (for MySQL)
│   │   ├── pg_dump (for PostgreSQL)
│   │   ├── RMAN (for Oracle)
│   │   ├── SQL Server Management Studio (for MS SQL)
│   │   └── Third-Party Tools (e.g., Percona, Veeam)
│   └── Disaster Recovery Planning
│       ├── High Availability (HA) Strategies
│       └── Testing and Documentation of Backup/Restore Process
│
├── 5. Database Security
│   ├── Access Control
│   │   ├── Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)
│   │   ├── User Authentication (LDAP, Kerberos)
│   │   └── Privilege Management (GRANT, REVOKE)
│   ├── Data Encryption
│   │   ├── At Rest (TDE - Transparent Data Encryption)
│   │   ├── In Transit (SSL/TLS)
│   └── Auditing and Compliance
│       ├── Auditing Logs
│       └── Compliance (GDPR, PCI DSS, HIPAA)
│
├── 6. Query Optimization and Performance Tuning
│   ├── Query Optimization
│   │   ├── Understanding Execution Plans
│   │   ├── Index Optimization (B-Tree, Hash Indexes)
│   │   ├── Query Refactoring and Best Practices
│   │   └── Avoiding Common Pitfalls (e.g., N+1 Queries)
│   ├── Performance Tuning
│   │   ├── Database Caching (Query Cache, Buffer Pool)
│   │   ├── Connection Pooling
│   │   ├── Partitioning (Range, List, Hash)
│   │   └── Table Compression
│   └── Monitoring Tools
│       ├── MySQL Workbench (MySQL)
│       ├── pgAdmin (PostgreSQL)
│       ├── Oracle Enterprise Manager
│       ├── SQL Server Profiler
│       └── Third-Party Tools (Percona Monitoring, SolarWinds)
│
├── 7. High Availability and Replication
│   ├── Database Replication
│   │   ├── Master-Slave Replication
│   │   ├── Master-Master Replication
│   │   └── Synchronous vs. Asynchronous Replication
│   ├── High Availability (HA)
│   │   ├── Clustering (MySQL Cluster, PostgreSQL Replication)
│   │   ├── Failover Strategies
│   │   └── Load Balancing
│   └── Disaster Recovery
│       ├── Hot, Warm, and Cold Standbys
│       └── Automated Failover with Tools (e.g., Pacemaker, Corosync)
│
├── 8. Cloud Databases
│   ├── AWS
│   │   ├── RDS (MySQL, PostgreSQL, Oracle, SQL Server)
│   │   ├── DynamoDB (NoSQL)
│   │   └── Aurora (Managed Database Service)
│   ├── Azure
│   │   ├── Azure SQL Database
│   │   ├── Cosmos DB (NoSQL)
│   └── GCP (Google Cloud Platform)
│       ├── Cloud SQL (MySQL, PostgreSQL, SQL Server)
│       └── Firestore (NoSQL)
│
├── 9. Database Monitoring and Maintenance
│   ├── Health Checks
│   │   ├── Checking Resource Usage (Memory, CPU, Disk)
│   │   ├── Database Size and Growth Patterns
│   ├── Automation
│   │   ├── Automating Backups and Restores
│   │   ├── Automating Routine Tasks (Scripts, Cron Jobs)
│   └── Monitoring Tools
│       ├── Zabbix
│       ├── Prometheus + Grafana
│       ├── Nagios
│       ├── Percona Monitoring and Management (PMM)
│       └── CloudWatch (AWS)
│
├── 10. Database Scaling
│   ├── Vertical Scaling
│   │   └── Scaling Up Resources (CPU, RAM)
│   ├── Horizontal Scaling
│   │   ├── Sharding
│   │   ├── Read Replicas
│   │   └── Database Clustering
│   └── Distributed Databases
│       ├── MongoDB Sharding
│       └── Cassandra Clusters
│
├── 11. DevOps and DBA Collaboration
│   ├── Infrastructure as Code (IaC) for Databases
│   │   ├── Terraform
│   │   ├── Ansible
│   └── CI/CD Pipelines for Databases
│       ├── Schema Migration Tools (Flyway, Liquibase)
│       └── Automated Testing and Rollbacks
│
├── 12. Soft Skills and Communication
│   ├── Documentation (SOPs for DB Management)
│   ├── Collaboration with Dev and Ops Teams
│   ├── Incident Response and Root Cause Analysis
│   └── Security and Compliance Reporting
